<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation" xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">
    <Paragraph Style="{DynamicResource HeaderParagraphStyle}">
        Virtualization Demo
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph >
        This sample implements virtualization to improve the performance while zooming and loading in a map. Only the shapes that are shown will be loaded; other parts of the map outside of the viewing area will be unloaded from the panel.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph TextAlignment="Center">
        <Image Source="Image\VirtualizationDemo.png" Stretch="None"/>
    </Paragraph>
	<Paragraph  FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16" TextAlignment="Center">
Fig: <Bold> Virtualization Demo </Bold>
</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Style="{DynamicResource HeaderParagraphStyle}">
        Features
    </Paragraph>
    <List Margin="25,0,0,0">
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>Enable and disable the virtualization feature.</Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>Only the shapes that are shown will be loaded; other shapes outside of the viewing area will be unloaded from the panel.</Paragraph>
        </ListItem>

    </List>
    <Paragraph Style="{DynamicResource HeaderParagraphStyle}">
        Interactions
    </Paragraph>
    <List Margin="25,0,0,0">
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>Select or clear the
                <Bold>EnableVirtualization</Bold> check box to enable or disable virtualization in the map.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>Zoom and pan in the map until some of shapes are outside of the view port of the map.</Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>Now zoom or pan the map. The zooming and panning performance has been improved.</Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
    </List>
</FlowDocument>